msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/time_integration.rst:357
#: ec15961ac29f47efb76d203ea0cc79a3
msgid "the condensed inner block, ``condenser(K)[0]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/time_integration.rst:358
#: 6d3f9b6e884147d3b0dbd32122e843a7
msgid "``pre_solve_rhs(f)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/time_integration.rst:359
#: 4c129167b9dc41d88d8b6973e97899f0
msgid "once per stage RHS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/time_integration.rst:360
#: 60e1b454a8aa42bcbb7d10abcffebe6e
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"the *restriction* to inner DOFs, ``condenser.restrict(f)`` — **not** "
"``condense_rhs(f)``: a stage slope is zero on the boundary by "
"construction, so the :math:`-K_{io}\\,u_o` correction term in "
"``condense_rhs`` would over-apply the BC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/time_integration.rst:365
#: bb1735cba00e4349a00b7793fc17517f
msgid "``recover_stage(k_i)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/time_integration.rst:366
#: b2a5343b2afa48d09dd346d63b9e1706
msgid "once per stage, after the solve"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/time_integration.rst:367
#: 2a9808ae8c894f4eaf76c5fc4c5dbd7a
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"the prolongation to full DOF with zero in the boundary slots, "
"``condenser.prolong(k_i)`` — **not** ``recover``, which would write the "
"Dirichlet value into the boundary slots and break the increment ``u_{n+1}"
" = u_n + h\\sum_i b_i k_i``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/time_integration.rst:372
#: aa1d5d5e1e3a4a06988fb430d73bf45b
msgid ""
"The fourth hook, ``post_solve(u)``, runs after the stage slopes have "
"already been lifted and combined with :math:`u_0`, so ``u`` is always "
"full-DOF when it sees you. Use it for things that act on the final state "
"(clamping, normalisation, projection onto a manifold) rather than for "
"boundary recovery."
msgstr ""

